rComments: Mr Levesque is a good teacher and know what he talks about. His lectures are very important in order to succeed the class. Personally, I found it hard to follow everything he says, he's all over the place sometimes, but I enjoyed his class of history of sports at UQAM
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Tough grader', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: Mr Levesque is still teaching, now at UQAM, and sadly his lectures have not improved at all. I am quite impressed with the amount of time he was able to waste on (usually funny) Monty Python jokes and boring movie excerpts. Very friendly though.

I agree he's a really nice guy, but not a good lecturer. However, I gradually found that the lectures were *so* boring that they were elevated to an art form. Once I passed that threshold of understanding, I enjoyed the classes thoroughly.
